basics

  • no gender

  • relativly normal tenses
  • plural you
  • plural it
  • question suffix
    • ko
  • or versus xor

noun cases

  • noun conjugation
  • yay

opening sentence to the usa foreign service institutes 1968 classic, the finnish graded reader:

karhulla oli juustonpala suussa

the bear had a piece of cheese in its mouth

  • el oso tena un trozo de queso en la boca
  • the bear had a piece of cheese in its mouth
  • bear mouth was holding a cheese

technical stuff

vowel harmony

back vowels
a, o, u
front vowels
, , y
middle vowels
e, i

consonant gradation

some sounds only work as the final consonant in a word

  • mp -> mm
  • nt -> nn
  • lt -> ll

kirjakieli ja puhekieli

  • dont conjugate verbs the same way
  • dont use they
  • dont use past tense
  • just ignore all the middle letters. they dont matter
    • sin -> s, s, sie, n
  • some of the ending letters too
  • new question suffix
    • ks
